erse at Heartbeat\n|\nHe held her hand and shook his head. 'They're inside, part of us by now. They are us. Where can we escape?\n\n- Greg Bear, Blood Music\n|\nA professional who doesn't deliver as committed is not just lazy, he is a liar.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nThere are many good things in the world, but not all of them benefit you. Focus keeps you on the path of what is right and away from other options.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nShe had been proud of his decision to serve his country, her heart bursting with love and admiration the first time she saw him outfitted in his dress blues.\n\n- Nicholas Sparks, The Lucky One\n|\nYou cannot reach success only by working hard, you also need to be working smart.\n\n- Charbel\n|\nThis is what comes of having a heart, even a very small and young one. It causes no end of trouble, and that’s the truth.\n\n- Catherynne M. Valente, The Girl Who Fell Beneath Fairyland and Led the Revels There\n|\nA melancholy-looking man, he had the appearance of one who has searched for the leak in life's gas-pipe with a lighted candle.\n\n- P.G. Wodehouse, The Man Upstairs and Other Stories\n|\nYou know my name, not my story. You've heard what I've done, but not what I've been through.\n\n- Jonathan Anthony Burkett, Neglected But Undefeated\n|\nFor to be free is not merely to cast off one's chains, but to live in a way that respects and enhances the freedom of others.\n\n- Nelson\n|\nNever hesitate to let the one you love know how you feel. Align your minds, synchronise your hearts and above be fearless when dancing with their souls.\n\n- Truth Devour, Wantin\n|\nBefore you eat the elephant, make sure you know what parts you want to eat.\n\n- Todd Stocker, Refined: Turning Pain Into Purpose\n|\nIf we grow in faith, we shall never seize to bear fresh fruit.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nGreat journey, great joy.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nBut the purpose of the book is not the horror, it is horror's defeat.\n\n- Terry Pratchett, Good Omens: The Nice and Accurate Prophecies of Agnes Nutter, Witch\n|\nOh darling, don't be bitter. It's the first instinct of the weak.\n\n- Sarah Dessen, Along for the Ride\n|\nLook at the people around you. Some Inspire you, some Perspire you. Be with those that build Energy in you.\n\n- RVM\n|\nYou were the missing piece of my soul, the breath in my lungs, and the blood in my veins.\n\n- J.A. Redmerski, The Edge of Never\n|\nI said: 'A line will take us hours maybe;Yet if it does not seem a moment's thought,Our stitching and unstitching has been naught.\n\n- W.B.\n|\nWas it worth it? My death, I mean. Did I die for something worthwhile?\n\n- Elizabeth Carlton, Chivalry's Code\n|\nWhen God wins your heart, He has won it forever.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nEnjoy without injury, live without loss.\n\n- Amit\n|\nIf happiness were the means to measure the evolutionary level of a species, I bet Darwin would’ve changed his mind and places humans at the very bottom.\n\n- Charbel\n|\nLife is magnificent and vivacious, but it is also fugacious.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nDo not only think about it, but feel about it, also, before taking appropriate action.\n\n- T.F. Hodge, From Within I Rise: Spiritual Triumph Over Death and Conscious Encounters with 'The Divine Presence'\n|\nAs for the tokens whereof thou ask me, I may tell thee of them in part: but as touching thy life, I am not sent to shew thee.\n\n- Compton\n|\nThe welkin is blue yet in agony,The air and the water has made a pair,As the love was unfaithful and the earth has to suffer, until the time goes backwards.\n\n- J.\n|\nPeople say everybody has a book inside them, so why not make your life a great story?\n\n- Martha\n|\nSo does he live, seeking, finding, joying and suffering.\n\n- Kate\n|\nIf heaven is tolerant and writers are allowed (bunch of liars though they are), I wonder if they gather for coffee to ponder the prose they should have written instead.\n\n- Lori Lansens, The Girls\n|\nThey say religion is about l